Scores of personnel of Nigerian Police Force have laid siege at the National Secretariat of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) in Abuja. The protesters, who had gathered to protest against the APC National Chairman, Adams Oshiomhole, started attacking each other over a yet-to-be ascertained issue. Details later… Kogi: 20 APC gov’ship aspirants reject indirect primary PDP protesters pass vote-of-no confidence on panel handling Atiku's petition Protesters storm APC secretariat, demand Oshiomhole’s resignation